Subject: [PATCH] patch 0881: institutional capex narrative + management mix
 extractor
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replaces the "specifics not detailed" filler from 0879 with structured
multi-field extraction so the Capex line carries amount + location +
timeline + phase + funding + purpose - not adjectives.

extractCapexNarrative scans ALL cleaned sentences (not just the single
keyMentions quote) for:
  amounts:   ₹ X Cr / Rs Y crore / INR Z mn (multiple capture)
  locations: 60+ Indian industrial-cluster names (Tarapur, Vizag, etc)
  timelines: FY26 / H1FY27 / Q2FY27 / etc
  phases:    Phase I / Phase II + context word
  funding:   debt / internal accrual / equity raise / QIP
  purpose:   new products / debottleneck / capacity expansion / etc
  type:      growth | maintenance | mixed | unspecified
  topSentence: highest-scoring capex-relevant sentence

extractManagementMix scans for institutional-quality positive +
cautious sentences using anchor patterns (record print / consecutive
growth / margin expansion / guidance raised / order book growth / new
customers / pricing power / commercial production / leverage kicking
in / volume momentum versus delay / input shortage / margin pressure
/ headwinds / demand slowdown / input cost spike / guidance cut /
macro pressure / one-time charge / pricing pressure / MTM hit).
Each candidate must also pass scoreSentence>=3 AND contain either a
number or a strong verb, so generic chatter never surfaces.

buildTopLineVerdict now reads concall.capexNarrative + managementMix
and stitches them into the Capex line and Why-mixed line, replacing
the inline single-quote extractor from 0879.

For NGL Fine Chem the Capex line should now read something like:
  "Capex: GROWTH - Phase I contributing - Phase II - 210 Cr at
   Tarapur - 182.75 Cr invested - commercial H2FY27 - funded by debt
   + internal accruals - for new products in pipeline + capacity
   expansion"
And the Why-mixed line should pull "consecutive growth" + "commercial
production" snippets on the positive side, "delay" + "input shortage"
on the cautious side - the actual concall sentences with numbers,
not "take the information on record".
